=== Etymology ===
{{etystub}}
From {{Gr.}} [[ίσος]] ("equal") + [[τόπος]] ("place").

===Noun===
'''isotope'''
#One of two or more [[atom]]s of an [[element]] having the same number of [[proton]]s, but a different number of [[neutron]]s in its [[nucleus]]. As a [[consequence]], it will have the same [[atomic number]] but a different [[mass number]] ([[atomic weight]]).

